Interface Expression<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of value this expression returns
    All Superinterfaces:
    SyntaxElement
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Literal<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CondExprCompare, CondExprIsSet, ConditionalExpression, ConvertedExpression, ExprArguments, ExprBinaryMathFunctions, ExprBooleanOperators, ExpressionList, ExprLoopValue, ExprNumberArithmetic, ExprRange, ExprUnaryMathFunctions, ExprWhether, LiteralList, LitMathConstants, SimpleLiteral, Variable, VariableString

    public interface Expression<T>
extends SyntaxElement
    An expression, i.e a SyntaxElement representing a value with some type.

        T[] getValues(TriggerContext ctx)

        Parameters:
        ctx - the event
        Returns:
        an array of the values

      • acceptsChange

        @Nullable
default @Nullable java.lang.Class<?>[] acceptsChange(ChangeMode mode)
        Determines whether this expression can be changed according to a specific ChangeMode, and what type of values it can be changed with.
        Parameters:
        mode - the mode this Expression would be changed with
        Returns:
        an array of classes describing what types this Expression can be changed with, or null if it shouldn't be changed with the given change mode. If the change mode is ChangeMode.DELETE or ChangeMode.RESET, then an empty array should be returned.

      • isLoopOf

        default boolean isLoopOf(java.lang.String s)
        When this expression is (possibly) looped, returns what the "loop type" (as in loop-<loop type>) should be in order to describe each element of the values of this expression.
        Parameters:
        s - the "loop type"
        Returns:
        whether the given "loop type" describes this expression's elements. By default, returns true if the parameter is "value"
        See Also:
        ExprLoopValue, Loop
